%C - formats concatenated input

%C [-width] [-w width] [-m maximum] [-] [files]...
Options:
 width    - tries to have lines as close as possible to width.
 maximum  - lines cannot be longer than maximum.
 -        - read from standard input
Note:
 length defaults to 65 and the maximum to 75.  Non-indent tabs are
 converted to spaces.  Tabs are used for indents where possible.
 If no input files are given, standard input is read.
